div.div:
Perspective Shapes
This is an example of a perspective set, created by distortions from the origin, which is an average or undifferentiated perspective.
In the context of religion, 'spiritual' might be an average perspective.
The perspectives are generated by distortion functions & priorities, which transform the original perspectives toward different intents & structures.
Perspectives can also be framed as a filter - a perspective focuses on some information & leaves out others, so the filter generating that focus can be the perspective object (rule set) itself.
